            <h3>Mission Statement</h3>
            Our mission is to support homeschool families in Kitsap County by providing 
            sports education and Christian character development through friendly athletic competition. <br /><br />
            <h3>Club Description </h3>
            We are a Christian homeschool organization, dedicated to developing positive attitudes in an encouraging environment. 
            &ensp;We are an all volunteer organization, with our coaching staff and board consisting of parents of participating players.<br /><br />  

            We currently offer three sports: soccer in the fall, basketball in the winter, and baseball in the spring.&ensp;
            Soccer and baseball practices and games are held at a local park in Port Orchard.&ensp;Basketball is held at a 
            middle school gymnasium in Port Orchard. <br /><br />

            For each sport, our players are assigned to a group determined by their age, and each age group is divided into 
            teams for practices and games.&ensp;We have one practice day and one game day each week, and each season runs for 10 weeks.  
            &ensp;At the end of the season, we hold an awards ceremony where each player receives an award for participation.
